<item>
            <title>[CAMEL-15460] FTP Reconnect not successful</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CAMEL-15460</link>
                <project id="12311211" key="CAMEL">Camel</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;This is a follow-up of&#160;issue&#160;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CAMEL-15299&quot; title=&quot;FTP endpoints will silently not delete/move file on disconnect&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;CAMEL-15299&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;CAMEL-15299&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;During&#160;&lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/camel/blob/master/components/camel-ftp/src/main/java/org/apache/camel/component/file/remote/FtpOperations.java#L1015&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;reconnect&lt;/a&gt;&#160;currently the expectation is that NOOP command throws an exception in case the client is not connected to the server anymore, but it might also just return false when not successful. During debugging I found that there is still a pending command (eg. retrieve of a file) which should be read before the NOOP, otherwise the NOOP response is not read correctly.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Will prepare a PR.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
